Class ExifExtractor

java.lang.Object
  |
  +--jpo.ExifExtractor
All Implemented Interfaces:
ExifTagValues
public class ExifExtractor
extends Object
implements ExifTagValues

Extracts Exif data from a JPEG header segment, providing information about the camera/scanner/capture device (if available). Information is encapsulated in an ImageInfo object.

Author:
Drew Noakes http://drewnoakes.com

motorollaByteOrder

private boolean motorollaByteOrder
Represents the native byte ordering used in the JPEG segment. If true, then we're using Motorolla ordering (Big endian), else we're using Intel ordering (Little endian).

convertBytesToVersionString

private String convertBytesToVersionString(int tagValueOffset)
Takes a series of 4 bytes from the specified offset, and converts these to a well-known version number, where possible. For example, (hex) 30 32 31 30 == 2.10).

Parameters:
tagValueOffset - the offset at which the first version byte exists
Returns:
the version as a string of form 2.10

convertTagToNumber

private double convertTagToNumber(int offset,
                                  int formatCode)
Evaluates the value at the given offset, assuming the provided format code. Values are returned as double primitives, which should be cast to the desired type.

Format codes are FMT_BYTE, FMT_URATIONAL, FMT_DOUBLE, etc...
